        p Jonagold is a cultivar of apple developed in 1953 at the New York State Agricultural Experiment Station of Cornell University's College of Agriculture and Life Sciences. It is a cross between the crisp Golden Delicious and the blush-crimson Jonathan. The name "Jonagold" is a portmanteau of these two variety names.

